Andrew R
Kuching30 contributions
3.0 of 5 bubbles
Understand what you will get
A two day one night typical “cruise” will give you 22 hours in the bay. With up to 12 hours of darkness you’ll see the bay for just over 10 hours. The cruise boat you booked will be moving in the bay for 2-3 hours, and there will be another 2 or so hours moving on a small day boat for excursions.

There are three groups of boats, one for each of Ha Long, Lan Ha and Bai Tu Long Bay. Only the smaller Halong bay registered boats can dock at Halong Bay harbour. The others are reached by a small day boat.
Each cruise boat has a designated point A where they anchor overnight and a point B they go to during the day. Arriving at lunch time you will move very slowly from A to B, anchor and go on an excursion, then move back from B to A to anchor overnight.
There will be another excursion in the morning, then you’ll go back to shore by the day boat, or on the cruise boat if it’s one for Ha Long bay that’s small enough.
This applies to most cruises. Some cruise boats that are smaller move about more because they have more flexibility and don’t use a day boat for excursions. By small I mean under 10 cabins.
Relatively few people book a 3 day 2 night cruise. If you do on one of the larger more luxurious boats they don’t change their itinerary but send you of Kayaking and swimming on another small day boat for the extra day. You will move around your chosen bay a little more, but maybe not a lot. Each night will still be at the cruise boats point A.
The land/sea scape is stunning in good weather. In grey cloudy weather with low visibility it’s still very atmospheric. But the boats, especially the small ones, are not brilliant at keeping you warm in winter.
If you don’t go in an excursion from the bigger boats you will see the tenders arriving with laundry, food and to pump out the waste.
The trip from Hanoi is longer than you think. It’s 2.5 hours drive in Google maps, but it’s 4 or more when you figure in multiple hotel pick ups, the obligatory stop at the pearl market, and the wait at the quayside until everyone has arrived.
Written January 27, 2024
